        "\n",
        "The small screen estate space of mobiles phones and smart watches necessitates displaying content in a dynamic manner. Virtual reality glasses (called AR/VR or XR in marketing speak) need dynamic content because the user is able to move around the environment. These are questions that interaction design is called upon to solve. @hoangEnterDynamicIsland2022: *\"Dynamic interfaces might invoke a new design language for extended reality\". it's a balancing at: while* AI enables generative UIs while users need some type of stability (think: text input stays in the same place but different types of interfaces appear within a clearly defined space.\n",
        "\n",
