        "The Wellbeing Economy Alliance (WEAll) countries (New Zealand, Iceland, Finland, Scotland, Wales) as well as the EU and Canada, started the coalition in 2018 looking to involve more broad-based metrics in developing their societies[@ellsmoorNewZealandDitches2019; @davidsuzukifoundationWellbeingEconomies2021; @ceprFairSustainableProsperous2022; @scottishgovernmentWellbeingEconomyGovernments2022; @wellbeingeconomyallianceWhatWellbeingEconomy2022].\n",
